WEBVTT

00:08.800 --> 00:11.088
ROZ: Hi, Niles.
- Hey, Roz.

00:11.260 --> 00:12.505
Hey, how's Daphne?

00:12.678 --> 00:15.429
Actually, l just got back
from visiting her at the spa.

00:15.596 --> 00:16.627
ROZ: Yeah.
- lt wasn't easy,

00:16.806 --> 00:20.173
but she has already lost
9 pounds and 1 2 ounces.

00:20.350 --> 00:23.100
Wow, good for her.
lt's all about will power.

00:23.268 --> 00:25.723
NlLES: Yeah.
- Oh, thanks.

00:26.604 --> 00:29.272
l'm going back to the spa this coming
weekend, if you need a ride.

00:30.231 --> 00:31.262
These aren't for me.

00:31.441 --> 00:34.476
Alice's school is having a picnic,
and l'm bringing the goodies.

00:34.651 --> 00:37.106
Yes, so l see.
Just don't get them sunburned.

00:37.278 --> 00:39.982
l'm sorry. lt's just--

00:40.197 --> 00:42.272
Well, aren't you a little overdressed
for a picnic?

00:42.448 --> 00:45.282
Well, there is this cute
single dad named Greg.

00:45.450 --> 00:47.323
- Oh.
- He's going through a divorce.

00:47.493 --> 00:50.493
His wife cheated on him.
He's so nice too.

00:50.662 --> 00:52.987
He deserves a woman he can trust.

00:53.164 --> 00:55.239
Do these look like l baked them?

00:56.124 --> 00:59.077
Yes, just as long as they don't taste
like you baked them.

01:01.545 --> 01:02.624
- Gotta go.
- All right.

01:02.796 --> 01:03.874
- Hi, Roz.
ROZ: Hey, Frasier.

01:04.046 --> 01:05.670
Can l get a latte to go, please?

01:05.839 --> 01:09.172
Well, Niles, it's official,

01:09.342 --> 01:12.959
our old high school
is on the verge of bankruptcy.

01:13.178 --> 01:15.134
What happened
to the fundraising committee?

01:15.304 --> 01:17.095
We disbanded it this morning.

01:18.515 --> 01:20.174
- l don't believe it.
FRASlER: Yeah.

01:20.349 --> 01:22.840
- Bryce Academy gone.
- Mm-hm.

01:23.018 --> 01:25.010
- No more third-floor library.
- No.

01:25.186 --> 01:26.265
No more science lab.

01:26.437 --> 01:31.678
Oh, gosh, l stole my first kiss
in that science lab.

01:31.857 --> 01:34.312
Jill Solomon.
She was pretty upset about it,

01:34.484 --> 01:37.852
but l was beaming all the way
to the nurse's office.

01:38.487 --> 01:40.775
No more nurse's office.

01:40.947 --> 01:44.445
l spent many
a happy gym class there.

01:44.658 --> 01:47.823
- Frasier, we can't let this happen.
- l don't see how we can prevent it.

01:47.993 --> 01:51.408
Believe me, there are no more
alumni arms left to be twisted.

01:51.579 --> 01:54.365
Well, maybe we're twisting
the wrong arms.

01:54.540 --> 01:57.907
We know plenty of people who give
to any cause that comes along.

01:58.084 --> 01:59.163
FRASlER:
Perhaps you're right.

01:59.335 --> 02:01.540
Let's get some of that cash
flowing Bryce's way.

02:01.711 --> 02:03.869
How soon we can get
our well-to-do friends together?

02:04.046 --> 02:06.536
No time to waste, Niles.
How's Wednesday evening?

02:06.715 --> 02:08.872
No, can't. Theatre tickets.
How about Thursday?

02:09.050 --> 02:10.543
An appointment at the spa.

02:10.717 --> 02:12.709
- Well, can you change it?
- Well, not willingly.

02:12.886 --> 02:15.292
lt's with the good masseur,
the blind one.

02:16.138 --> 02:18.046
He's blind.

02:18.223 --> 02:22.136
When he said he couldn't see clients,
l thought he was just booked all week.

02:25.561 --> 02:28.016
We should probably talk strategy
before the guests get here.

02:28.188 --> 02:29.895
Yes, all right,
we don't wanna pounce.

02:30.064 --> 02:32.186
Let's let them get settled in,
have a few cocktails,

02:32.357 --> 02:34.148
and then,
when they're sufficiently relaxed,

02:34.317 --> 02:37.021
we'll shear them like Delilah.

02:37.194 --> 02:38.225
[DOORBELL RlNGS]

02:38.403 --> 02:39.434
Our first guest.

02:39.612 --> 02:42.316
Let the fundraising begin.

02:44.282 --> 02:46.654
Hello, one and all.
Please come in, please come in.

02:46.826 --> 02:48.734
Thank you for coming.
Let me take your wrap.

02:48.910 --> 02:50.701
Here we are.
Please make yourselves at home.

02:50.870 --> 02:52.862
MAN: The place looks wonderful.
FRASlER: Thank you.

02:53.038 --> 02:54.746
- l love that painting.
- Really?

02:54.914 --> 02:57.914
lt's hardly as impressive as that portrait
that Hockney did of your wife.

02:58.083 --> 02:59.198
- You like it?
- Mm-hm.

02:59.376 --> 03:01.035
- Make me an offer.
- Excuse me?

03:01.210 --> 03:04.045
Between you and me,
l'm getting hammered by margin calls.

03:04.213 --> 03:05.243
[DOORBELL RlNGS]

03:05.422 --> 03:06.999
Need a watch?

03:07.173 --> 03:09.461
Oh, actually, that's not really--

03:09.633 --> 03:14.175
Oh, Mertzie. Oh, good to see you.
How is everything?

03:14.345 --> 03:16.835
So the judge voided our prenup,
and if that's not bad enough,

03:17.013 --> 03:18.637
l'm paying half her lawyer's fee.

03:18.806 --> 03:22.589
These Russian gals look good
on the lnternet, but...

03:26.436 --> 03:28.262
How are things going
on your side of the room?

03:28.438 --> 03:29.896
Not very well.

03:30.064 --> 03:32.139
Seems Marshall sank
all his money into a new house.

03:32.315 --> 03:36.063
Sally sank all her money
into a new boat, which sank.

03:36.652 --> 03:39.486
Wait, Niles, the door. lsn't that--?

03:39.654 --> 03:41.231
Oh, yes, it is. Eleanor Lynch.

03:41.405 --> 03:43.480
l heard she got a huge settlement
from the Mariners

03:43.656 --> 03:45.483
after that baseball bat flew
into the stands--

03:45.658 --> 03:49.737
No, no, no, the woman next to her.
lsn't that Penelope Janvier?

03:49.911 --> 03:52.827
Of the Penelope Janvier Foundation?
Oh, yes, it is.

03:52.996 --> 03:54.454
Niles, this is amazing luck.

03:54.622 --> 03:57.409
She could write a cheque covering
the amount without batting an eye.

03:57.583 --> 03:59.740
Don't put it that way
in front of Eleanor.

04:00.335 --> 04:01.959
- Let's go talk to her.
- No, no, wait.

04:02.127 --> 04:04.452
We're only gonna have one crack.
We'd better make it good.

04:04.629 --> 04:07.546
- Let's devise a plan. Come with me.
- All right, all right.

04:07.840 --> 04:10.081
- Oh!
- Oh, goodness, are you all right?

04:10.258 --> 04:11.503
Oh, l just twisted my ankle.

04:11.676 --> 04:14.344
Well, well, sit down.
l'll take this back to the kitchen for you.

04:14.511 --> 04:16.716
Oh, thank you.

04:16.887 --> 04:20.884
Hey, sweetheart.
Need some more Crunch 'n Munch.

04:21.057 --> 04:23.345
- Oh, l'm not a--
MARTlN: l'm sorry.

04:23.517 --> 04:25.177
l'm sure you're busy,

04:25.352 --> 04:27.474
but if my sons see me traipsing
through their party,

04:27.645 --> 04:31.476
they'll think l'm gonna embarrass them
in front of all their stuffed-shirt friends.

04:33.691 --> 04:36.015
You look familiar.

04:36.193 --> 04:38.434
You ever dance?

04:42.780 --> 04:45.780
- Now, we've got to appear casual.
- Should we start with small talk?

04:45.949 --> 04:47.408
Perhaps, perhaps.
Oh, yes, you know,

04:47.575 --> 04:50.030
l recall an aphorism that's usually
attributed to Santayana,

04:50.202 --> 04:52.029
but l have my own little version.

04:52.204 --> 04:53.318
We've got to get out there.

04:53.496 --> 04:56.247
Give me a chance to get the words.
''Money cannot so enrich a man--''

04:56.415 --> 04:58.703
- She's talking to Dad.
- Let's get the hell out there.

05:00.209 --> 05:02.082
Dad, what happened
with that woman just now?

05:02.252 --> 05:04.328
Nothing. She got a phone call
and she had to leave.

05:04.504 --> 05:06.828
- She said to say thanks.
- Come off it. You offended her.

05:07.006 --> 05:10.836
What was it, Dad?
A bawdy joke? Nose whistling?

05:11.008 --> 05:13.084
Do you have any idea who that was?

05:13.260 --> 05:17.091
Yes, she said her name was
Penelope Janvier or Janvier or--

05:17.263 --> 05:19.468
Janvier, Dad.
Jan, Jan-- Oh, it doesn't matter.

05:19.639 --> 05:21.430
Well, it does to me.

05:21.599 --> 05:24.136
l wanna say her name right
if we're having dinner tomorrow.

05:24.684 --> 05:29.179
- You didn't ask her out, did you, Dad?
- No, she asked me out.

05:29.354 --> 05:31.975
l'm sorry, Dad.
lt's just that l'm a little shocked.

05:32.148 --> 05:33.346
l think that's pronounced:

05:33.524 --> 05:37.057
''Sorry, Dad,
l'm a condescending jackass.''

05:45.157 --> 05:47.363
NlLES: Dad left to meet
Penelope five hours ago.

05:47.533 --> 05:49.324
What could they be doing?

05:49.868 --> 05:52.441
l can think of one possibility.

05:52.912 --> 05:55.367
You think-- On a first date?

05:55.539 --> 05:58.658
Niles, they went to a steak house.
Penelope's paying.

05:58.833 --> 06:01.667
l'm sorry, but l don't think
a 48 ouncer is out of the question.

06:05.004 --> 06:08.502
You know, Niles, hard to believe,

06:08.673 --> 06:13.215
but Penelope Janvier could actually
become Dad's girlfriend.

06:13.385 --> 06:15.424
Well, that's not so preposterous.

06:15.594 --> 06:18.132
Mom was as cultured
and intelligent as they come

06:18.305 --> 06:19.964
and he certainly made her happy.

06:20.139 --> 06:21.930
That he did.

06:22.099 --> 06:23.890
You know,
it might be good for Dad too.

06:24.059 --> 06:25.434
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

06:25.643 --> 06:28.394
lt certainly won't hurt
our fundraising efforts.

06:28.562 --> 06:30.139
- For Bryce.
- For Bryce.

06:30.313 --> 06:31.890
[MARTlN AND PENELOPE
CHATTERlNG]

06:32.064 --> 06:33.309
He's back.

06:33.482 --> 06:34.810
ls that a woman's voice?

06:34.983 --> 06:38.433
My God, she came home with him.

06:39.903 --> 06:44.113
- Dad.
- Dad, hey, how was your evening?

06:44.281 --> 06:45.360
MARTlN:
Couldn't have gone better.

06:45.532 --> 06:46.611
FRASlER:
Dad, am l mistaken,

06:46.783 --> 06:49.273
or did we just hear the sound
of a woman's voice out here?

06:49.451 --> 06:52.024
Oh, yeah, she's in the powder room.
But, listen--

06:52.203 --> 06:54.872
The powder room? l haven't changed
the hand towels for three days.

06:55.038 --> 06:56.449
[NlLES TSKS]

06:56.623 --> 06:59.991
Don't you cluck your tongue at me.

07:02.210 --> 07:06.253
Estelle, l'd like you to meet my boys.
This is Frasier and Niles.

07:06.421 --> 07:07.963
- Hello.
- Nice to meet you guys.

07:08.131 --> 07:10.170
Lovely.

07:10.382 --> 07:12.006
Thanks for letting me use the john.

07:12.175 --> 07:14.084
Oh, sure.
So see you tomorrow, okay?

07:14.260 --> 07:15.374
Great.

07:20.139 --> 07:22.380
- Bye, guys.
- Bye-bye.

07:25.976 --> 07:29.179
l'm beat.
Well, see you guys tomorrow.

07:29.354 --> 07:31.061
BOTH:
Dad?

07:31.939 --> 07:34.773
Oh, all right. Here's what happened.

07:34.941 --> 07:37.431
Penelope and l got along great,
but after l dropped her off,

07:37.609 --> 07:39.897
l was still hungry.
So l went to this little coffee shop

07:40.069 --> 07:41.693
near McGinty's
to get some chilli fries.

07:41.862 --> 07:44.779
Now, l know what you're wondering.
Doesn't McGinty's have chilli fries?

07:44.948 --> 07:46.607
Yes, and they're very tasty.

07:46.782 --> 07:49.451
Who the hell is Estelle?

07:49.618 --> 07:51.693
She works at the coffee shop.
We got chatting,

07:51.869 --> 07:54.406
the next thing you know,
we're having a nightcap at McGinty's.

07:54.579 --> 07:57.034
Hey, when it rains, it pours.

07:57.206 --> 07:58.949
Yes, Dad, but what about Penelope?

07:59.124 --> 08:02.124
- Oh, l'm seeing her Tuesday.
- You just made a date with Estelle.

08:02.293 --> 08:04.285
Not for Tuesday.

08:05.045 --> 08:06.788
You're gonna date both of them?

08:06.963 --> 08:09.169
- Are you sure that's wise?
- Well, it's just dating.

08:09.340 --> 08:12.043
l met them both at the same time.
l like them both.

08:12.217 --> 08:14.837
- Where's the harm in it?
- Don't you think it's a little risky?

08:15.010 --> 08:16.753
What if one of them
should find out about--

08:16.928 --> 08:18.386
- Penelope, for example.
- Yes, yes.

08:18.554 --> 08:20.380
You wouldn't want
to alienate her permanently.

08:20.556 --> 08:23.306
Oh, don't worry.
l've watched you juggle.

08:23.474 --> 08:26.095
l've got a pretty good handle
on what not to do.

08:32.230 --> 08:33.972
- Oh, hi, Niles.
- Hey, Roz.

08:34.649 --> 08:37.269
Off to another picnic, l see.

08:37.442 --> 08:39.184
Yeah, Greg and l
are really hitting it off.

08:39.360 --> 08:40.640
He loves my cooking.

08:40.820 --> 08:42.562
l'm sorry, miss,
we're out of lemon bars.

08:42.738 --> 08:44.231
Well, make some more.

08:44.405 --> 08:47.489
And give me a dirty pan.
l need to put it in my sink.

08:47.658 --> 08:50.064
l'm sorry. Our baker
doesn't come in until tomorrow.

08:50.243 --> 08:53.611
- l can give you the recipe.
- What am l supposed to do with that?

08:54.829 --> 08:58.660
- Bake?
- ls that supposed to be funny?

09:02.334 --> 09:04.326
Good Lord, Niles.
You won't believe this.

09:04.503 --> 09:07.040
''Bryce trustees
are already reviewing a proposal

09:07.213 --> 09:09.169
for the purchase of their land.''

09:09.339 --> 09:12.292
Dad just walked in. Let's drop
another hint about meeting Penelope.

09:12.466 --> 09:14.672
Time for hints has passed.
We've got to be direct.

09:14.843 --> 09:17.214
Dad is not gonna let us
ask his girlfriend for money.

09:17.386 --> 09:20.589
l didn't say honest. l said direct.
Try to keep up, for God's sakes.

09:20.764 --> 09:21.843
MARTlN: Hey, guys.
- Hey, Dad.

09:22.015 --> 09:24.090
Have a seat. Have a seat.

09:24.266 --> 09:26.258
So-- Wow, is that espresso?

09:26.434 --> 09:29.434
Yeah, a little ''pick me up''
in between dates.

09:29.603 --> 09:32.722
Boy, this juggling thing
isn't as easy as l make it look.

09:32.897 --> 09:34.095
But don't you worry.

09:34.273 --> 09:39.064
<i>They're both getting first-class passage
on the S.S. Martin.</i>

09:39.235 --> 09:41.642
Oh, that's where you get that from.

09:42.195 --> 09:43.938
[CELL PHONE RlNGlNG]

09:44.322 --> 09:45.981
That's me.

09:46.156 --> 09:48.362
- You got a cell phone?
- Well, sure, l had to.

09:48.533 --> 09:51.153
You don't think l'm gonna give them
both my home number, do you?

09:51.326 --> 09:53.117
Come on, Fras, that's amateur hour.

09:53.745 --> 09:56.069
See l programmed the phone
for different rings

09:56.247 --> 09:59.081
depending on who's calling, so
that way l don't get caught off guard.

09:59.249 --> 10:01.999
Now this is William Tell.
Rhymes with Estelle.

10:03.627 --> 10:05.085
Hello.

10:05.253 --> 10:08.502
Oh, hi, Estenelope.

10:09.256 --> 10:12.754
Penelope? That's right.
Here son's name's William.

10:12.925 --> 10:16.340
Yeah. Oh, sure,
Tuesday sounds great.

10:16.511 --> 10:18.668
Pick me up at 7? Okay.

10:18.845 --> 10:21.845
See you then, Penelope.

10:22.014 --> 10:25.762
- That was very smooth.
- Yes, yes.

10:25.934 --> 10:28.258
Dad, about Penelope,
actually, we were wondering...

10:28.435 --> 10:29.763
[CELL PHONE RlNGlNG]

10:29.936 --> 10:32.391
Now, you see, that's Estelle.

10:33.022 --> 10:37.232
Hello? Hey, Estelle,
l had a feeling it might be you.

10:38.526 --> 10:40.601
Tuesday at 7? Sounds great.

10:40.777 --> 10:43.861
- Yeah, oh, hold on a sec. What?
- Didn't you just make a date

10:44.029 --> 10:45.108
for Tuesday with Penelope?

10:45.280 --> 10:47.272
- That was Thursday?
- No, we both heard Tuesday.

10:47.448 --> 10:49.903
Oh, thanks.
Boy, that could've been ugly.

10:50.075 --> 10:53.443
Yeah, Estelle, no, sorry.
Thursday's out. lt has to be Tuesday.

10:53.619 --> 10:55.907
- No, no, no.
- No, wait, wait.

10:56.079 --> 10:58.285
Thursday. Thursday's what l meant.

10:58.456 --> 11:02.405
Yeah. Okay, talk to you later. Bye.

11:02.584 --> 11:06.532
She's got it bad, and that ain't good.

11:07.796 --> 11:09.076
FRASlER:
Dad, uh...

11:09.255 --> 11:13.880
Dad, listen, we were thinking it might
be time that we meet Penelope.

11:14.050 --> 11:15.544
She sounds enchanting.

11:15.718 --> 11:18.291
- Yeah, enchanting. How's tomorrow?
- Oh, guys, l don't know.

11:18.470 --> 11:21.505
You know, meeting the family.
That's taking it up another notch.

11:21.680 --> 11:23.304
l don't wanna get that serious yet.

11:23.473 --> 11:27.221
Maybe in a few months, but right now
l just wanna keep it simple.

11:27.393 --> 11:29.800
Simple? As in Estenelope?

11:32.104 --> 11:34.855
Hello. Who's that?

11:35.023 --> 11:37.098
Dad, for God's sake,

11:37.274 --> 11:39.017
isn't there enough
on your plate as it is?

11:39.192 --> 11:43.520
What can l tell you?
Daddy's got a big appetite.

11:47.532 --> 11:50.532
Dear God, what do we do now?

11:50.700 --> 11:53.191
Oh, l don't know.
l guess we could have him neutered.

11:54.328 --> 11:57.826
l suppose we could try to get
to Penelope through her foundation.

11:57.997 --> 12:01.163
l already tried that, and there's a
six-month waiting list just to see her.

12:01.333 --> 12:02.743
[CELL PHONE RlNGlNG]

12:02.917 --> 12:03.996
Lord, Dad left his phone.

12:04.168 --> 12:06.575
Maybe l'd better run
and tell him it's Penelope.

12:08.087 --> 12:10.660
You know, l'll never catch him.

12:10.839 --> 12:15.132
No, he's long gone and would probably
want you to take a message.

12:16.760 --> 12:18.669
Hello.

12:18.845 --> 12:21.133
No, this is his son, Frasier.

12:21.305 --> 12:25.467
Penelope Janvier?
Oh, well, how nice to speak with you.

12:25.975 --> 12:27.599
A cocktail party?

12:27.768 --> 12:30.554
Tomorrow night. He'll be there.

12:30.728 --> 12:34.096
ln fact, l'll make sure of that.
l'll be driving him myself.

12:34.272 --> 12:38.518
You see, my brother, Niles,
and l will be with him all day.

12:38.692 --> 12:41.360
lt's our once-a-year family day,

12:41.527 --> 12:44.278
and we do
just about everything together.

12:45.405 --> 12:48.820
What's that? Are you sure? Really?

12:48.991 --> 12:51.825
Well, then, yes, we'd love to come.

12:58.997 --> 13:01.073
FRASlER: My, Penelope
certainly has good taste.

13:01.249 --> 13:03.158
Well, of course.
She likes Dad, doesn't she?

13:03.334 --> 13:04.744
Oh, can it.

13:04.918 --> 13:06.957
l'm still mad at you guys
for inviting yourselves.

13:07.128 --> 13:09.914
Now, remember, be careful
what you say in front of Penelope.

13:10.088 --> 13:14.085
l got a delicate balancing act
going on here, so don't mess it up.

13:14.258 --> 13:15.337
Don't mess what up?

13:15.509 --> 13:18.675
Oh, hi. Why, your lovely living room.

13:18.845 --> 13:22.094
My boys really like to rough house.

13:24.265 --> 13:27.715
All right, Penelope,
these are my sons, Niles and Frasier.

13:27.892 --> 13:30.465
Hello. We spoke on the phone.
lt's such a pleasure to meet you.

13:30.644 --> 13:32.636
- Thank you.
- Dad speaks about you all the time.

13:32.812 --> 13:33.927
Yes.

13:34.105 --> 13:35.184
[CELL PHONE RlNGlNG]

13:35.356 --> 13:39.602
Oh, that's just my alarm
to remind me to take my pills.

13:39.776 --> 13:41.056
Let's get you a glass of water.

13:41.235 --> 13:44.069
No, no, that's all right.
l'd rather do it in private. Thank you.

13:44.237 --> 13:46.608
Yeah, he has trouble swallowing.

13:47.489 --> 13:49.861
- A small epiglottis.
- Yeah.

13:50.033 --> 13:53.566
Epiglottis. l haven't heard that word
since biology class in high school.

13:53.744 --> 13:56.530
- Oh, yes. High school.
- Yeah.

13:56.704 --> 13:59.159
- lt's a pity about our old high school.
PENELOPE: Oh, William.

14:00.623 --> 14:04.323
Niles, Frasier,
l'd like you to meet my son, William.

14:04.501 --> 14:06.410
- Hello.
- Nice to meet you.

14:06.586 --> 14:08.127
These are Marty's boys.

14:08.295 --> 14:09.410
Oh.

14:09.588 --> 14:10.702
Hi.

14:12.215 --> 14:15.049
Did l just hear Dr. Corman
ask you for $50,000

14:15.217 --> 14:17.043
for a new CAT scan machine
at the hospital?

14:17.218 --> 14:18.628
lt is a worthy cause.

14:18.802 --> 14:19.965
Yes, mother, they all are,

14:20.137 --> 14:23.386
but it's inappropriate to hit you up
for money at a party.

14:23.556 --> 14:26.342
Teddy was your father's
closest friend.

14:26.516 --> 14:28.841
Bourbon was my father's
closest friend.

14:29.018 --> 14:30.476
l showed Ted out.

14:30.644 --> 14:33.181
William, he delivered you.

14:33.354 --> 14:36.687
- Excuse me, l have to go get him.
- Yes, all right.

14:37.357 --> 14:39.598
People look at my mother,
all they see is dollar signs.

14:39.775 --> 14:40.890
- lt makes me sick.
- Yeah.

14:41.068 --> 14:42.312
What are you guys doing here?

14:42.485 --> 14:44.857
Us? Oh, well, actually,
your mother invited us.

14:45.029 --> 14:46.855
- She did.
- Uh-oh.

14:47.030 --> 14:49.022
Mother's been cornered
by Father Patterson.

14:49.198 --> 14:51.570
Or should l say Father Sponge.

14:54.869 --> 14:56.576
NlLES:
Oh, my goodness.

14:56.745 --> 14:58.903
lt's gonna be hard pressing our case
with him around.

14:59.080 --> 15:01.749
Don't worry, Niles. We'll get a chance.
We've got all night.

15:01.916 --> 15:03.742
Don't get too comfortable,
we've gotta leave.

15:03.917 --> 15:06.490
- What?
- l had a date with Estelle tonight,

15:06.669 --> 15:08.163
and she's been waiting
a half an hour.

15:08.337 --> 15:10.210
lt's not like me to screw up like this.

15:10.380 --> 15:13.131
What about Penelope, Dad?
You cannot just walk out on her party.

15:13.298 --> 15:16.501
Hey, Estelle took the evening off
special just to be with me, you know?

15:16.676 --> 15:18.217
And she's pretty steamed.

15:18.385 --> 15:21.255
Rules of the game,
angriest woman wins.

15:21.929 --> 15:22.960
[CELL PHONE RlNGlNG]

15:23.138 --> 15:26.138
- Oh, good Lord.
- Jeez. Grab your coats.

15:26.307 --> 15:27.386
PENELOPE: Frasier?
- Yes.

15:27.558 --> 15:31.175
- Where's your father off to?
- He had to take more pills.

15:31.352 --> 15:33.925
My goodness, l had no idea
he was on so much medication.

15:34.104 --> 15:38.315
- Are you concerned?
- Well, not really. No, he'll be fine.

15:38.482 --> 15:41.732
l just wish l could say the same
for our old high school.

15:41.901 --> 15:44.308
- What are you three talking about?
- Um...

15:44.528 --> 15:45.903
William, there you are.

15:46.071 --> 15:48.822
Excuse us. l just wanted to alert you
to a possible situation.

15:48.990 --> 15:51.610
l overheard one of the servers
discussing a one-act play

15:51.783 --> 15:53.491
he wants your mother to produce.

15:53.660 --> 15:57.110
- Okay, which one?
- l think it was something by Chekhov.

15:57.287 --> 15:59.362
The long and the short of it is,
Mrs. Janvier,

15:59.539 --> 16:05.954
is that my alma mater,
Bryce Academy, is in dire straits.

16:06.126 --> 16:09.909
The coffers are bare,
and our only hope is to find a saviour.

16:10.088 --> 16:13.253
Forgive me for being presumptuous,
but l was hoping it might be you.

16:13.423 --> 16:16.423
Actually, l'm familiar with Bryce.

16:16.592 --> 16:19.627
Well, then you must also be familiar
with their excellent standards.

16:19.803 --> 16:22.968
Yes, l am.
They wouldn't let in William.

16:23.138 --> 16:28.641
Well, with your endowment,
l'm sure he'd be a shoo-in.

16:29.101 --> 16:35.635
No, l'm sorry, Miss Janvier.
Please, we are desperate.

16:36.564 --> 16:38.437
Ordinarily,
l wouldn't even consider this,

16:38.607 --> 16:42.189
but l'm very fond of your father.

16:42.360 --> 16:45.028
Call the foundation tomorrow
with the details,

16:45.195 --> 16:46.570
and we'll issue you a cheque.

16:46.738 --> 16:48.564
Thank you, thank you.
That's very kind of you.

16:48.739 --> 16:51.027
- Thank you so much.
- lt's my pleasure.

16:51.199 --> 16:53.357
l'd do anything for your father.
He's a rarity.

16:53.534 --> 16:55.941
FRASlER: Mm-hm.
- He's an old-fashioned gentleman.

16:56.119 --> 16:58.195
Well, l gotta go.

16:59.705 --> 17:02.824
- Marty, what's wrong?
- Feeling a little under the weather.

17:02.999 --> 17:04.790
Well, then maybe
you ought to see my doctor.

17:04.959 --> 17:07.247
- He's here at the party.
- No, l don't need a doctor.

17:07.419 --> 17:10.039
Those were
my husband's last words.

17:10.212 --> 17:12.288
- Don't leave.
- All right, if you insist.

17:12.464 --> 17:14.704
Pull the car around.
l'm going out through the kitchen.

17:14.882 --> 17:17.454
We can't leave right now.
Penelope will get suspicious.

17:17.634 --> 17:18.796
Estelle's already suspicious.

17:18.968 --> 17:21.044
l've decided
to break it off with Penelope.

17:21.220 --> 17:22.762
- What?
- Hearing Estelle just now,

17:22.929 --> 17:24.921
how upset she was on the phone,
it made me realise

17:25.098 --> 17:26.212
how much l cared about her.

17:26.390 --> 17:30.387
All right, listen, Dad,
Bryce Academy is going bankrupt.

17:30.560 --> 17:33.264
Penelope is going to write
a cheque tomorrow to save it.

17:33.437 --> 17:36.437
So until then, l need you to pretend
that you're still interested in her.

17:36.605 --> 17:38.230
l can't believe this.

17:38.398 --> 17:40.474
You and your brother
have been using me.

17:40.650 --> 17:43.603
Martin, this is Dr. Corman.

17:43.777 --> 17:46.813
Well, it's nice to meet you, but
l'm feeling a lot better now. Thanks.

17:46.988 --> 17:52.028
lf l let you leave without knowing
if you're sick, l'll worry all night.

17:52.200 --> 17:54.654
And you wouldn't want that,
now, would you, Dad?

17:54.826 --> 17:57.198
- Here we are.
- Oh, all right. All right.

17:57.370 --> 17:59.825
Doctor, be thorough.

17:59.997 --> 18:03.080
MARTlN:
But the pants stay on.

18:03.249 --> 18:06.202
Ms. Janvier, l realise
that l've been a little pushy.

18:06.376 --> 18:09.329
Oh, not pushy.
Just assertive. l like that.

18:09.503 --> 18:14.662
Oh, well, then be prepared to love me
because l need that cheque right now.

18:14.840 --> 18:16.666
Was it this one? Devilled-egg guy?

18:16.842 --> 18:18.170
NlLES:
Uh...

18:18.843 --> 18:19.922
You know, l'm not sure.

18:20.094 --> 18:22.549
He and chicken-satay guy
look so much alike.

18:23.179 --> 18:24.721
All right, listen up.

18:24.889 --> 18:27.805
Which one of you snack jockeys
is trying to get a play produced?

18:32.686 --> 18:35.141
FRASlER: Miss Janvier,
thank you again so much.

18:35.313 --> 18:37.388
Just make it out to Bryce Academy.

18:37.564 --> 18:39.224
- Do you have a pen?
- Oh, yes, of course.

18:39.399 --> 18:41.474
You know, when you sign
as many autographs as l do,

18:41.650 --> 18:42.895
you always have to have your--

18:43.068 --> 18:47.017
- Oh, good Lord.
- Never mind. William, l need a pen.

18:47.196 --> 18:49.271
- What for?
- l'm writing a cheque.

18:49.447 --> 18:50.526
Oh, that's it.

18:50.698 --> 18:53.532
We're going down to the special room,
and we're gonna talk about this.

18:53.700 --> 18:54.815
[NlLES SlGHS]

18:59.955 --> 19:01.662
Mother, l--

19:01.831 --> 19:04.451
Mother,
l forbid you to write another cheque.

19:04.624 --> 19:05.822
Oh, just give me a pen.

19:06.000 --> 19:08.076
l don't have one.

19:10.670 --> 19:12.662
Mother.

19:12.838 --> 19:14.747
This could be
an elaborate scheme to bilk us.

19:14.923 --> 19:16.417
You don't know who these guys are.

19:16.591 --> 19:19.046
- We're Marty's boys.
- And l trust Martin.

19:19.260 --> 19:20.374
[CELL PHONE RlNGlNG]

19:20.552 --> 19:24.002
- Oh, that's Martin's alarm.
- Just ignore that.

19:24.638 --> 19:28.137
- This is a phone.
- Well, here, l'll take it.

19:30.267 --> 19:35.177
Hello? Well, this is Penelope.
Who's this?

19:35.354 --> 19:38.105
Estelle, Martin's girlfriend?

19:40.524 --> 19:42.315
May l take a message?

19:42.484 --> 19:44.393
Pill time! Time for more pills.

19:45.319 --> 19:47.358
l'll tell him.

19:47.529 --> 19:50.979
Estelle says don't bother
coming over tonight.

19:51.157 --> 19:53.149
Oh, Marty, how could you?

19:53.325 --> 19:56.609
l'm sorry.
l was gonna tell you but...

19:56.785 --> 19:59.655
l guess this means
breakfast Tuesday is off.

19:59.829 --> 20:03.114
That's right. And it was Thursday.

20:04.416 --> 20:07.285
- l don't need this pen anymore.
- Miss Janvier, please.

20:07.459 --> 20:08.870
l don't blame you for being angry,

20:09.044 --> 20:10.703
but if you believe
in the hope of tomorrow

20:10.878 --> 20:14.745
and a brighter future, then please,
please don't punish the children

20:14.923 --> 20:17.460
of Bryce Academy for our misdeeds.

20:17.633 --> 20:18.878
Oh, boo-hoo.

20:20.844 --> 20:22.800
- Mother.
- That's enough, William.

20:22.970 --> 20:26.219
l made a promise to these men,
and l'm a woman of my word.

20:26.389 --> 20:27.966
Oh, thank you. Thank you so much.

20:28.140 --> 20:29.967
You are more gracious
than we deserve.

20:30.142 --> 20:32.513
Yes, thank you.

20:34.395 --> 20:35.474
Well done, Frasier.

20:35.646 --> 20:37.638
Oh, Niles, l can't wait
to see the expression

20:37.814 --> 20:42.972
on the headmaster's face
when he sees this cheque for $50.

20:43.151 --> 20:44.977
What?

20:45.152 --> 20:46.812
Well, l--

20:46.987 --> 20:51.813
l guess it's $50
more than we had before.

20:51.990 --> 20:54.029
Well, let's go, fellas.
Grab my coat, will you?

20:54.200 --> 20:55.575
Right, Dad.

